<br>
I have a webpage where I post humourous picture based stories of Transformers and other toys (<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.angelfire.com/apes/grcrosscut/toypics">right here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, if you're curious)  and for my next story, two Transformers get imported from Japan, and well, they speak Japanese! The only problem is that I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> can't</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> speak japanese. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  For a gag, I used an online translator, pictures of kanji Translated by Babelfish, and added an extra &quot;u&quot; to a bunch of words for my <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.angelfire.com/apes/grcrosscut/toypics/youken/indexu.html">April Fool's Day Special</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> (which is bound to unintentionally offened any Japanese person who happened to read the site, sorry!) but for this story, even extrememly simple Japanese (in english letters like &quot;A b c&quot;) would be nice. <br>
<br>
Anyhoo, the segments I need Translated are (in quotations) as follows: <br>
<br>
Galvatron: &quot;Hey, this is not the Bahamas!&quot; (and for the next caption he says...) &quot;Who are you people? What are we doing here? I demand that you answer me immeidately!&quot;<br>
<br>
Corahda: &quot;I told you that we should not have used discount airlines! Did I not tell you that?&quot;<br>
<br>
Galvatron:&quot;Oh be quiet!&quot; (or &quot;shut up&quot; or whatever the Japanese equivalent of this would be). <br>
<br>
And later on they shout:<br>
<br>
Galvatron: &quot;Look it! It is right behind us!&quot;<br>
Corahda: &quot;Run away! Run away!&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
And also, is there a Japanese equivalent of an &quot;Ooooooooo&quot; or &quot;Ahhhhhhh&quot; of amazement or surprise? I could use that too, if anyone has it handy. <br>
<br>
Huge thanks in advance!<br>
<br>
---<br>
GR Crosscut<br>
